@andfoy, please:

1. Remove reference to conda-forge because now pywinpty can be installed from the defaults channel.
2. Update the compilation process to mention that we now use mingw.

The module name is `winpty` but the package is named pywinpty.

We should have both names be the same, in this case I would lean towards `pywinpty`

@ccordoba12 what do you think?
